INSERT INTO `feeds_data_classifieds_import` VALUES ('181','104','1270078950','http://westernmass.craigslist.org/web/1670867548.html','http://westernmass.craigslist.org/web/1670867548.html','Email Marketing Specialist (Williamstown MA)','Located in Williamstown, J.F.Griffin Publishing, LLC is the leading publisher of official state hunting &  fishing regulation magazines in the U.S. The company reaches more sportsman in the eastern united states than most major sporting magazines combined. Our company works exclusively with state Fish & Wildlife Agencies, creating the best official regulation publications available for sporstmen, while saving Fish & Wildlife agencies time and money.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nEmail Marketing Specialist\n<br>\nIn this lead position, you will use your expertise in developing, executing and launching outbound email campaigns; you will help create and implement our email transactional and marketing strategy as well as generate effective email campaigns, including promotional offers, newsletters, and custom campaigns. \n<br>\nYou will contribute to the ongoing strategy & marketing of the email campaigns to our state partners, and help create the necessary materials for the sales staff.\n<br>\nYou should possess both business & proven web design skills.\n<br>\n	Create, launch and ensure the quality of effective email advertising campaigns.\n<br>\n	Manage and maintain a full understanding of the email platform, including the management of lists, unsubscribe and compliance process, etc.\n<br>\n	Manage ad trafficking & reporting.  \n<br>\n	Manage all aspects of deliverability reporting, including seed lists, report setup, results monitoring, and program optimization based on reported results.\n<br>\n	Generate and disseminate all email campaign reporting including deliverability, (bounces, spam complaints, inbox) and performance (opens, clicks, responses).\n<br>\n	Be the subject matter expert on email best practices and continuously look for opportunities to optimize existing programs and capitalize on untapped opportunities.\n<br>\n	Maintain current knowledge through external opportunities, including webinars and conferences.\n<br>\n	Be a customer experience, privacy, and anti-spam compliance advocate and help others find the balance between short-term promotional needs and long-term, healthy customer relationships and assure\n<br>\nstrong deliverability results.\n<br>\n	Provide feedback on email volume, timing and frequency, as well as eMail content (graphics and copy) to ensure successful results and alignment with best practices.  \n<br>\n\n<br>\n Experience in email marketing or a relevant discipline, such as Marketing, Advertising, Graphic Design, Fine Arts, or Computer-related Design, equivalent experience may be considered.\n<br>\n	2 years of stable, professional experience in well-conceived, optimized eMail advertising campaign development and implementation.\n<br>\n	Demonstrated expertise in eMail best practices including privacy and anti-spam policies, eMail effectiveness, testing, optimization, segmentation and list management.\n<br>\n	Good command of HTML, and the internal and external tools used to build and send eMail.\n<br>\n	Self motivation with the ability to juggle many tasks at once and focus effort as needed, depending on relative priority and criticality.\n<br>\n	Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate concepts in a clear and effective manner.\n<br>\n');
