INSERT INTO `feeds_data_classifieds_import` VALUES ('180','111','1270320276','http://westernmass.craigslist.org/reo/1674969238.html','http://westernmass.craigslist.org/reo/1674969238.html','Pre-Renovation Country Condo (Williamstown, MA) $349900 3bd','Pre-Renovation Offering  Two Condo Units at Williamstowns historic Minnie Mansion  1541 Green River Road, Williamstown, MA 01267 - the convenience of condo living in a private, country setting with mountain views.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nTwo spacious luxury units available now in the final stages of being meticulously restored.  Each unit will have an all new energy-efficient Buderus furnace and radiator system, new Anderson windows, new kitchens with Frigidaire Gallery stainless-steel appliances and granite counter-tops, laundry room with built-in ironing boards, new bathrooms with Kohler bathroom fixtures and Moen faucets, beautiful hardwood and tile floors throughout.  Both units have working fireplaces in the living room.  All new plumbing, new roof, new exterior paint, new everything!\n<br>\n\n<br>\nFront Unit:  3 bedrooms, 1 bathrooms (all new), full basement, with possibility of an attic entertainment room/office, garage, front porch, private yard.  1617 sq. ft.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nRear Unit:  3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms (all new), full basement, entertainment room/office adjacent to master bedroom, garage, porch, private yard. 1859 sq. ft.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nPre-renovation price of $349,900 for each unit.  During the renovation buyers will have a limited opportunity to make choices on fixtures, paint colors, granite counter-top colors, etc.  In spite of being an old house, these units - inside and out - will be in a nearly \"like new\" condition at the completion of the renovation, and thus will require minimal maintenance for many years to come\n<br>\n\n<br>\nThis charming house was built in 1915 as part of Williamstown\'s historic Mount Hope Farm complex and until recently was owned by Williams College.  These wonderful condo units are in a unique location accessible to great walking trails.  There is nothing quite like these two units in the northern Berkshires.  Drive to skiing at Jiminy Peak in 15 minutes, music at Tanglewood in 45 minutes, modern art at MassMOCA in 20 minutes.  20 minutes to Pittsfield, 50 minutes to Albany.  Great location!\n<br>\n\n<br>\nNOTE TO REAL ESTATE AGENTS :  Although this is a For Sale by Owner property, buyers agents will be paid an attractive commission.  You are also invited to drop by to review the property any time during renovation.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nNOTE TO OTHERS:  If you introduce us to a buyer, we will pay you a finder\'s fee.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nBefore the condo conversion is made, the entire property is also available to a single buyer.  Call to inquire about the price.\n<br>\n\n<br>\nPrices will go up in May when the property is listed with a realtor.  \n<br>\n\n<br>\nCall 413-347-9099 for more information or a showing.');
