INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('358','358','1','Apr 12: Theodore Roosevelt and the Creation of the Modern Presidency','8:00 p.m., Griffin 7.<br /> <p>Sidney M. Milkis is the White Burkett Miller Professor of the Department of Politics and Assistant Director for Academic Programs at the Miller of Public Affairs at the University of Virginia.  His books include: <em>The President and the Parties: The Transformation of the American Party System Since the New Deal</em> (1993); <em>Political Parties and Constitutional Government: Remaking American Democracy</em> (1999); and <em>Presidential Greatness</em> (2000), coauthored with Marc Landy. He is also author of <em>The American Presidency: Origins and Development, 1776-2007</em> (2007), 5th edition, coauthored with Michael Nelson; and <em>Theodore Roosevelt, the Progressive Party, and the Transformation of American Democracy</em> (2009). <a href=\"/leadership/events/\">More...</a></p>','8:00 p.m., Griffin 7.<br /> <p>Sidney M. Milkis is the White Burkett Miller Professor of the Department of Politics and Assistant Director for Academic Programs at the Miller of Public Affairs at the University of Virginia.  His books include: <em>The President and the Parties: The Transformation of the American Party System Since the New Deal</em> (1993); <em>Political Parties and Constitutional Government: Remaking American Democracy</em> (1999); and <em>Presidential Greatness</em> (2000), coauthored with Marc Landy. He is also author of <em>The American Presidency: Origins and Development, 1776-2007</em> (2007), 5th edition, coauthored with Michael Nelson; and <em>Theodore Roosevelt, the Progressive Party, and the Transformation of American Democracy</em> (2009). <a href=\"/leadership/events/\">More...</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270513220','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('356','356','1','Apr 10: Faculty Recital: Nat Parke, Cello','8:00 p.m., Brooks Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>Cellist Nat Parke performs works baroque, classical and modern:  Bach Suite for Cello No. 4 in E-flat, Brahms: Violin Sonata No. 1, arranged for cello in D major, Samuel Barber Sonata for Cello and Piano, as well as the Hindemith Sonata for Solo Cello.  Mr. Parke is accompanied by Elizabeth Wright, piano. <a href=\"http://music.williams.edu/node/1090\">More...</a></p>','8:00 p.m., Brooks Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>Cellist Nat Parke performs works baroque, classical and modern:  Bach Suite for Cello No. 4 in E-flat, Brahms: Violin Sonata No. 1, arranged for cello in D major, Samuel Barber Sonata for Cello and Piano, as well as the Hindemith Sonata for Solo Cello.  Mr. Parke is accompanied by Elizabeth Wright, piano. <a href=\"http://music.williams.edu/node/1090\">More...</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270513220','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('357','357','1','Apr 12: Convergence of the Sum of the Reciprocals of the Squares','1:00 p.m., Bronfman 106.<br /> <p>Math/Stats Department Colloquium by Edgar Kosgey \'10.  Evaluating the series 1 + 1/4 + 1/9 + 1/16 + ...proved to be a very difficult matter, and it would take a genius beyond that of the Bernoullis to determine its elusive sum. In this talk, we are going touse two methods to show that the sum of the series converges is &Pi;2/6.</p>','1:00 p.m., Bronfman 106.<br /> <p>Math/Stats Department Colloquium by Edgar Kosgey \'10.  Evaluating the series 1 + 1/4 + 1/9 + 1/16 + ...proved to be a very difficult matter, and it would take a genius beyond that of the Bernoullis to determine its elusive sum. In this talk, we are going touse two methods to show that the sum of the series converges is &Pi;2/6.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270513220','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('355','355','1','Apr 10: Korean Pop Culture Festival','6:00 p.m., Goodrich Hall.<br /> <p>Are you interested in Korean pop culture?  Do you like/are curious about Korean movies, K-dramas, Korean music, or Korean sports teams?  If so, make sure you come to the Korean Pop Culture Festival!  Sponsored by Koreans of Williams, the K-Pop Festival will feature fun activities, fabulous prizes, and the opportunity to immerse yourself in the amazing and colorful world of Korean pop culture!  In addition, plenty of complimentary Korean snacks and drinks will be served as well.  Bring a friend and come enjoy the wonders of Korean pop!  If you have any questions, they can be directed to Ireane Cao (10isc@williams.edu).</p>','6:00 p.m., Goodrich Hall.<br /> <p>Are you interested in Korean pop culture?  Do you like/are curious about Korean movies, K-dramas, Korean music, or Korean sports teams?  If so, make sure you come to the Korean Pop Culture Festival!  Sponsored by Koreans of Williams, the K-Pop Festival will feature fun activities, fabulous prizes, and the opportunity to immerse yourself in the amazing and colorful world of Korean pop culture!  In addition, plenty of complimentary Korean snacks and drinks will be served as well.  Bring a friend and come enjoy the wonders of Korean pop!  If you have any questions, they can be directed to Ireane Cao (10isc@williams.edu).</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270513220','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('354','354','1','Apr 10: Film: Gabrielle ','2:00 p.m., The Clark , 225 South Street.<br /> <p>Patrice Chreau adapts a Joseph Conrad story about the disintegrating marriage of a wealthy Parisian couple into a penetrating psychological study. Isabelle Huppert and Pascal Greggory inhabit the couple&rsquo;s vicious dilemma with wrenching intensity, even while the soire must go on. <a href=\"http://www.clarkart.edu/visit/press/content.cfm?ID=3219&year=2010\" target=\"_blank\">More...</a></p>','2:00 p.m., The Clark , 225 South Street.<br /> <p>Patrice Chreau adapts a Joseph Conrad story about the disintegrating marriage of a wealthy Parisian couple into a penetrating psychological study. Isabelle Huppert and Pascal Greggory inhabit the couple&rsquo;s vicious dilemma with wrenching intensity, even while the soire must go on. <a href=\"http://www.clarkart.edu/visit/press/content.cfm?ID=3219&year=2010\" target=\"_blank\">More...</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270513220','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('353','353','1','Apr 10: Kusika &amp; The Zambezi Marimba Band','8:00 p.m., MainStage, \'62 Center.<br /> <p>Kusika and the Zambezi Marimba Band will perform <em>Renewing the Spirit,</em> an evening of dance, music and poetry inspired by the people of New Orleans, Haiti, Chile, Southern Africa and here at home to endure hard times and renew ourselves. Music, dance and poetry inform us of who we were and who we can become on the journey. This year, Kusika set about creating new work around these themes and Zambezi studied Bob Marley, Fela Kuti and South African Jive compositions that urge us to keep moving toward the future. Please join us! Directed by Sandra L. Burton & Ernest D. Brown.  Tickets $3.  Call 413-597-2425 or visit the \'62 Center box office Tues.-Sat. 1-5 p.m.</p>','8:00 p.m., MainStage, \'62 Center.<br /> <p>Kusika and the Zambezi Marimba Band will perform <em>Renewing the Spirit,</em> an evening of dance, music and poetry inspired by the people of New Orleans, Haiti, Chile, Southern Africa and here at home to endure hard times and renew ourselves. Music, dance and poetry inform us of who we were and who we can become on the journey. This year, Kusika set about creating new work around these themes and Zambezi studied Bob Marley, Fela Kuti and South African Jive compositions that urge us to keep moving toward the future. Please join us! Directed by Sandra L. Burton & Ernest D. Brown.  Tickets $3.  Call 413-597-2425 or visit the \'62 Center box office Tues.-Sat. 1-5 p.m.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
