INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('398','398','1','Apr 11: Poverty Simulation','2:00 p.m. - 4:30 p.m., The Log, Spring Street.<br /> <p>Participants assume the roles of families facing poverty and learn what it is like to secure basic necessities or seek out social services. People who have personally experienced poverty will facilitate the event. Email <a href=\"mailto:lehmancouncil@gmail.com\">lehmancouncil@gmail.com</a> to reserve a spot! <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','2:00 p.m. - 4:30 p.m., The Log, Spring Street.<br /> <p>Participants assume the roles of families facing poverty and learn what it is like to secure basic necessities or seek out social services. People who have personally experienced poverty will facilitate the event. Email <a href=\"mailto:lehmancouncil@gmail.com\">lehmancouncil@gmail.com</a> to reserve a spot! <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('399','399','1','Apr 14: The Future of Living in the Northern Berkshires','7:30 p.m., Griffin 3.<br /> <p>How can we balance economic development and affordable living in imagining a future Northern Berkshires with more growth and less poverty? Don\'t miss this panel! Panelists include Dick Alcombright (Mayor of North Adams), David Rooney (President, Berkshire Economic Development Corporation), and Al Bashevkin (Executive Director, Northern Berkshire Community Coalition). <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','7:30 p.m., Griffin 3.<br /> <p>How can we balance economic development and affordable living in imagining a future Northern Berkshires with more growth and less poverty? Don\'t miss this panel! Panelists include Dick Alcombright (Mayor of North Adams), David Rooney (President, Berkshire Economic Development Corporation), and Al Bashevkin (Executive Director, Northern Berkshire Community Coalition). <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('400','400','1','Apr 15: Michael Curtin: Fighting Long-term Unemployment, Hunger, &amp; Poverty','7:30 p.m., Griffin 3.<br /> <p>A 1986 Williams alum (and former rugby team member), Michael Curtin is the CEO of D.C. Central Kitchen, a soup kitchen that serves over 4,000 meals a day and develops innovative strategies to combat long-term unemployment, hunger, and poverty. He will speak about his work and how a Williams education can be used to make a difference in the world. <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','7:30 p.m., Griffin 3.<br /> <p>A 1986 Williams alum (and former rugby team member), Michael Curtin is the CEO of D.C. Central Kitchen, a soup kitchen that serves over 4,000 meals a day and develops innovative strategies to combat long-term unemployment, hunger, and poverty. He will speak about his work and how a Williams education can be used to make a difference in the world. <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('401','401','1','Apr 16: Empty Bowl Dinner','5:30 p.m. and 7:00 p.m., First Congregational Church, 906 Main Street.<br /> <p>Proceeds from this fundraiser support the Berkshire Food Project, which serves meals to area residents experiencing food insecurity. Attendants can purchase unique, beautiful bowls hand-crafted by artisans and then feast on a variety of over 20 delicious soups! Email <a href=\"mailto:lehmancouncil@gmail.com\">lehmancouncil@gmail.com</a> for tickets (cost: $15) or to volunteer! Contact Laura Huang, unix: LH1 for further inquiry. <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','5:30 p.m. and 7:00 p.m., First Congregational Church, 906 Main Street.<br /> <p>Proceeds from this fundraiser support the Berkshire Food Project, which serves meals to area residents experiencing food insecurity. Attendants can purchase unique, beautiful bowls hand-crafted by artisans and then feast on a variety of over 20 delicious soups! Email <a href=\"mailto:lehmancouncil@gmail.com\">lehmancouncil@gmail.com</a> for tickets (cost: $15) or to volunteer! Contact Laura Huang, unix: LH1 for further inquiry. <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('402','402','1','Apr 16: Gym Class Heroes Concert','8:00 p.m., Towne Field House.<br /> <p>Gym Class Heroes mixes rock, hip-hop, soul, and punk to create a unique sound.  Signed to Fueled By Ramen and Decaydance Records, Gym Class Heroes has put out four albums since 2001 and has a new album coming out this year.  They have had four singles on Billboard&rsquo;s Hot 100 list.  The western Massachusetts-based band Stephen Kellogg and the Sixers will be opening for Gym Class Heroes. Sponsored by Williams College All Campus Entertainment.  Tickets are on sale at WilliamsTickets.com.</p><br /><a href=\'http://williamstickets.com\'>More &raquo;</a>','8:00 p.m., Towne Field House.<br /> <p>Gym Class Heroes mixes rock, hip-hop, soul, and punk to create a unique sound.  Signed to Fueled By Ramen and Decaydance Records, Gym Class Heroes has put out four albums since 2001 and has a new album coming out this year.  They have had four singles on Billboard&rsquo;s Hot 100 list.  The western Massachusetts-based band Stephen Kellogg and the Sixers will be opening for Gym Class Heroes. Sponsored by Williams College All Campus Entertainment.  Tickets are on sale at WilliamsTickets.com.</p><br /><a href=\'http://williamstickets.com\'>More &raquo;</a>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('403','403','1','Apr 17: Williams Great Day of Service!','10:30 a.m. - 4:00 p.m., various.<br /> <p>Give back to the community by volunteering with your friends, entry, or sports teams at work sites through-out the local area. Participants get bagged lunches, free t-shirts, and a pizza party dinner afterwards at The Log. Visit <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a> for more details and the online sign-up form!</p><br /><a href=\'http://engagement.williams.edu\'>More &raquo;</a>','10:30 a.m. - 4:00 p.m., various.<br /> <p>Give back to the community by volunteering with your friends, entry, or sports teams at work sites through-out the local area. Participants get bagged lunches, free t-shirts, and a pizza party dinner afterwards at The Log. Visit <a href=\"http://engagement.williams.edu\">engagement.williams.edu</a> for more details and the online sign-up form!</p><br /><a href=\'http://engagement.williams.edu\'>More &raquo;</a>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('404','404','1','Apr 17: Can and Should Courage and Independence of Mind be Taught?','12:30 p.m., Brooks-Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>Robert Gaudino believed that the experience of confronting the other, seeing the world through other people&rsquo;s eyes, and questioning all your assumptions, can produce moral human beings who demonstrate independence of mind and courage on behalf of  principle in the face of contrary pressure in personal and professional life.  And he believed that state of being can and should be taught to young adults in a classroom. Do you agree?   Moderator, Marty Linsky, &rsquo;61.  Panel includes Steve Lewis, &rsquo;60, Ellen Sherberg, &rsquo;70, Alan Schlosser, &rsquo;63, and Pam Carlton, &rsquo;76.  Part of a weekend of Gaudino Fund events.</p>','12:30 p.m., Brooks-Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>Robert Gaudino believed that the experience of confronting the other, seeing the world through other people&rsquo;s eyes, and questioning all your assumptions, can produce moral human beings who demonstrate independence of mind and courage on behalf of  principle in the face of contrary pressure in personal and professional life.  And he believed that state of being can and should be taught to young adults in a classroom. Do you agree?   Moderator, Marty Linsky, &rsquo;61.  Panel includes Steve Lewis, &rsquo;60, Ellen Sherberg, &rsquo;70, Alan Schlosser, &rsquo;63, and Pam Carlton, &rsquo;76.  Part of a weekend of Gaudino Fund events.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('405','405','1','Apr 17: Experiential Education: Past, Present, &amp; Future','2:15 p.m., Brooks-Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>This panel will include participants in Williams&rsquo; programs over the years, from Gaudino&rsquo;s in-India (Bill Loomis, &rsquo;71) and Guadino@Home (Jeff Thaler, &rsquo;74), to the relatively recent Williams-in-New York, to the very recent &ldquo;Resettling Refugees in Maine&rdquo; project (Bianca Martinez, &rsquo;12 & Charlotte Silverman, &rsquo;10) and the overseas Winter Study experiences from two Gaudino Fellows (Adam Century, &rsquo;12 & Meghan Rose Donnelly, &rsquo;11).  Moderator:  Ed Burger, Professor of Mathematics and Gaudino Scholar.</p>','2:15 p.m., Brooks-Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>This panel will include participants in Williams&rsquo; programs over the years, from Gaudino&rsquo;s in-India (Bill Loomis, &rsquo;71) and Guadino@Home (Jeff Thaler, &rsquo;74), to the relatively recent Williams-in-New York, to the very recent &ldquo;Resettling Refugees in Maine&rdquo; project (Bianca Martinez, &rsquo;12 & Charlotte Silverman, &rsquo;10) and the overseas Winter Study experiences from two Gaudino Fellows (Adam Century, &rsquo;12 & Meghan Rose Donnelly, &rsquo;11).  Moderator:  Ed Burger, Professor of Mathematics and Gaudino Scholar.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('406','406','1','Apr 17: Mark Hopkins Today: Professor Gaudinos Impact','3:45 p.m., Brooks Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>A wide range of alumni will give 5-10 minute presentations on the ways in which Prof. Gaudino had a life-long impact on them.  Participants include Matt Nimetz &rsquo;60, Counselor and Undersecretary at the State Dept, and as Personal Envoy for the UN Secretary General; Richard Brockman &rsquo;69, writer whose screenplay \"Good Behavior\" won a screenwriting/playwriting fellowship from the New York Foundation for the Arts.; Michael Morfit &rsquo;68, commissioned Foreign Service Officer with USAID, Vice President of Development Alternatives, Inc, and Visiting Professor and Georgetown University; James Mathieu &rsquo;72, commercial real estate broker with Contour Investment Properties in Jackson Hole, WY.</p>','3:45 p.m., Brooks Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>A wide range of alumni will give 5-10 minute presentations on the ways in which Prof. Gaudino had a life-long impact on them.  Participants include Matt Nimetz &rsquo;60, Counselor and Undersecretary at the State Dept, and as Personal Envoy for the UN Secretary General; Richard Brockman &rsquo;69, writer whose screenplay \"Good Behavior\" won a screenwriting/playwriting fellowship from the New York Foundation for the Arts.; Michael Morfit &rsquo;68, commissioned Foreign Service Officer with USAID, Vice President of Development Alternatives, Inc, and Visiting Professor and Georgetown University; James Mathieu &rsquo;72, commercial real estate broker with Contour Investment Properties in Jackson Hole, WY.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('407','407','1','Apr 17: Collecting the Thoughts of the Day on Great Teaching','4:45 p.m., Brooks-Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>A panel on how great teaching can and should change the way students see the world and how they live their lives.  And what it takes for this to happen.  Discussion led by former Gaudino Fund Chair, Richard Herzog, &rsquo;60.</p>','4:45 p.m., Brooks-Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>A panel on how great teaching can and should change the way students see the world and how they live their lives.  And what it takes for this to happen.  Discussion led by former Gaudino Fund Chair, Richard Herzog, &rsquo;60.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('408','408','1','Apr 20: MCC Canvas Project: Journey Woman','5:00 p.m., Jenness House.<br /> <p>The Williams College Multicultural Center (MCC) hosts an opening reception for the exhibit Journey Woman, on view from April 20-June 20. Helina Metaferia examines themes of identity and personal development through the figure. This exhibition features new mixed media paintings that celebrate spiritual journeys into self-discovery. Helina is the owner and founder of <a href=\"http://www.themetaexperience.com\" target=\"_blank\">The Meta Experience</a>, a visual and healing arts company. Also: artist talk and open meditation at noon in Hardy House. Lunch provided. More information: (413) 596-3340.</p>','5:00 p.m., Jenness House.<br /> <p>The Williams College Multicultural Center (MCC) hosts an opening reception for the exhibit Journey Woman, on view from April 20-June 20. Helina Metaferia examines themes of identity and personal development through the figure. This exhibition features new mixed media paintings that celebrate spiritual journeys into self-discovery. Helina is the owner and founder of <a href=\"http://www.themetaexperience.com\" target=\"_blank\">The Meta Experience</a>, a visual and healing arts company. Also: artist talk and open meditation at noon in Hardy House. Lunch provided. More information: (413) 596-3340.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270682273','0');
