INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('431','431','1','Apr 10: Korean Pop Culture Festival','6:00 p.m., Goodrich Hall.<br /> <p>Are you interested in Korean pop culture?  Do you like/are curious about Korean movies, K-dramas, Korean music, or Korean sports teams?  If so, make sure you come to the Korean Pop Culture Festival!  Sponsored by Koreans of Williams, the K-Pop Festival will feature fun activities, fabulous prizes, and the opportunity to immerse yourself in the amazing and colorful world of Korean pop culture!  In addition, plenty of complimentary Korean snacks and drinks will be served as well.  Bring a friend and come enjoy the wonders of Korean pop!  If you have any questions, they can be directed to Ireane Cao (10isc@williams.edu).</p>','6:00 p.m., Goodrich Hall.<br /> <p>Are you interested in Korean pop culture?  Do you like/are curious about Korean movies, K-dramas, Korean music, or Korean sports teams?  If so, make sure you come to the Korean Pop Culture Festival!  Sponsored by Koreans of Williams, the K-Pop Festival will feature fun activities, fabulous prizes, and the opportunity to immerse yourself in the amazing and colorful world of Korean pop culture!  In addition, plenty of complimentary Korean snacks and drinks will be served as well.  Bring a friend and come enjoy the wonders of Korean pop!  If you have any questions, they can be directed to Ireane Cao (10isc@williams.edu).</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('432','432','1','Apr 10: Faculty Recital: Nat Parke, Cello','8:00 p.m., Brooks Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>Cellist Nat Parke performs works baroque, classical and modern:  Bach Suite for Cello No. 4 in E-flat, Brahms: Violin Sonata No. 1, arranged for cello in D major, Samuel Barber Sonata for Cello and Piano, as well as the Hindemith Sonata for Solo Cello.  Mr. Parke is accompanied by Elizabeth Wright, piano. <a href=\"http://music.williams.edu/node/1090\">More...</a></p>','8:00 p.m., Brooks Rogers Recital Hall.<br /> <p>Cellist Nat Parke performs works baroque, classical and modern:  Bach Suite for Cello No. 4 in E-flat, Brahms: Violin Sonata No. 1, arranged for cello in D major, Samuel Barber Sonata for Cello and Piano, as well as the Hindemith Sonata for Solo Cello.  Mr. Parke is accompanied by Elizabeth Wright, piano. <a href=\"http://music.williams.edu/node/1090\">More...</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('433','433','1','Apr 13: Piano Concert: Wonny Song','8:00 p.m., Chapin Hall.<br /> <p>Wonny Song brings his versatile and intelligent performance style to our magnificent nine foot Bsendorfer grand piano.  A musician who has performed brilliantly all over the worlld, he brings us Bach: \"Schafe knnen sicher weiden\" from Cantata BWV 208; Schubert: Fantasy in C Major, \"Der Wanderer\", D.760, opus 15; Schubert/Liszt: Widmung; Debussy: Estampes; and Stravinsky: Suite from The Firebird.</p><br /><a href=\'http://music.williams.edu/node/1092\'>More &raquo;</a>','8:00 p.m., Chapin Hall.<br /> <p>Wonny Song brings his versatile and intelligent performance style to our magnificent nine foot Bsendorfer grand piano.  A musician who has performed brilliantly all over the worlld, he brings us Bach: \"Schafe knnen sicher weiden\" from Cantata BWV 208; Schubert: Fantasy in C Major, \"Der Wanderer\", D.760, opus 15; Schubert/Liszt: Widmung; Debussy: Estampes; and Stravinsky: Suite from The Firebird.</p><br /><a href=\'http://music.williams.edu/node/1092\'>More &raquo;</a>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
