INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('437','437','1','Apr 16: Gym Class Heroes Concert','8:00 p.m., Towne Field House.<br /> <p>Gym Class Heroes mixes rock, hip-hop, soul, and punk to create a unique sound.  Signed to Fueled By Ramen and Decaydance Records, Gym Class Heroes has put out four albums since 2001 and has a new album coming out this year.  They have had four singles on Billboard&rsquo;s Hot 100 list.  The western Massachusetts-based band Stephen Kellogg and the Sixers will be opening for Gym Class Heroes. Sponsored by Williams College All Campus Entertainment.  Tickets are on sale at WilliamsTickets.com.</p><br /><a href=\'http://williamstickets.com\'>More &raquo;</a>','8:00 p.m., Towne Field House.<br /> <p>Gym Class Heroes mixes rock, hip-hop, soul, and punk to create a unique sound.  Signed to Fueled By Ramen and Decaydance Records, Gym Class Heroes has put out four albums since 2001 and has a new album coming out this year.  They have had four singles on Billboard&rsquo;s Hot 100 list.  The western Massachusetts-based band Stephen Kellogg and the Sixers will be opening for Gym Class Heroes. Sponsored by Williams College All Campus Entertainment.  Tickets are on sale at WilliamsTickets.com.</p><br /><a href=\'http://williamstickets.com\'>More &raquo;</a>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('438','438','1','Apr 16: Williams Concert Choir: A German Requiem','8:00 p.m., Thompson Chapel.<br /> <p>Johannes Brahms\'s first great triumph during his lifetime, <em>Ein deutsches Requiem</em> for choir, orchestra and soloists is less a prayer for the dead and more a song of comfort, encouragement, and ultimately triumph for those who would grieve. The Concert Choir is directed by Brad Wells and is joined by soloist Keith Kibler, Kerry Ryer-Parke and a full orchestra.</p><br /><a href=\'http://music.williams.edu/node/1094\'>More &raquo;</a>','8:00 p.m., Thompson Chapel.<br /> <p>Johannes Brahms\'s first great triumph during his lifetime, <em>Ein deutsches Requiem</em> for choir, orchestra and soloists is less a prayer for the dead and more a song of comfort, encouragement, and ultimately triumph for those who would grieve. The Concert Choir is directed by Brad Wells and is joined by soloist Keith Kibler, Kerry Ryer-Parke and a full orchestra.</p><br /><a href=\'http://music.williams.edu/node/1094\'>More &raquo;</a>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('439','439','1','Apr 18: Artsbreak','1:00 p.m., The Clark.<br /> <p>The Department of Music presents Artsbreak. The sound of music pours from the gallery to enthrall art and music lovers alike as our students perform a wide variety of selections. Spend the afternoon gazing at the Degas sculpture \"Little Dancer Aged Fourteen\" while listening to music from Francine Clark&rsquo;s original piano.  This free event is open to the public. <a href=\"http://music.williams.edu/node/1013\">More...</a></p>','1:00 p.m., The Clark.<br /> <p>The Department of Music presents Artsbreak. The sound of music pours from the gallery to enthrall art and music lovers alike as our students perform a wide variety of selections. Spend the afternoon gazing at the Degas sculpture \"Little Dancer Aged Fourteen\" while listening to music from Francine Clark&rsquo;s original piano.  This free event is open to the public. <a href=\"http://music.williams.edu/node/1013\">More...</a></p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES ('440','440','1','Apr 20: MCC Canvas Project: Journey Woman','5:00 p.m., Jenness House.<br /> <p>The Williams College Multicultural Center (MCC) hosts an opening reception for the exhibit Journey Woman, on view from April 20-June 20. Helina Metaferia examines themes of identity and personal development through the figure. This exhibition features new mixed media paintings that celebrate spiritual journeys into self-discovery. Helina is the owner and founder of <a href=\"http://www.themetaexperience.com\" target=\"_blank\">The Meta Experience</a>, a visual and healing arts company. Also: artist talk and open meditation at noon in Hardy House. Lunch provided. More information: (413) 596-3340.</p>','5:00 p.m., Jenness House.<br /> <p>The Williams College Multicultural Center (MCC) hosts an opening reception for the exhibit Journey Woman, on view from April 20-June 20. Helina Metaferia examines themes of identity and personal development through the figure. This exhibition features new mixed media paintings that celebrate spiritual journeys into self-discovery. Helina is the owner and founder of <a href=\"http://www.themetaexperience.com\" target=\"_blank\">The Meta Experience</a>, a visual and healing arts company. Also: artist talk and open meditation at noon in Hardy House. Lunch provided. More information: (413) 596-3340.</p>','Created/updated by FeedsNodeProcessor','1270728727','0');
